            <title><![CDATA[Pokémon Is Releasing Some Incredible Merch For Gold And Silver’s 25th Anniversary]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/pokemon-is-releasing-some-incredible-merch-for-gold-and-1851700355</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/pok%C3%A9mon-is-releasing-some-incredible-merch-for-gold-and-silver%E2%80%99s-25th-anniversary.1036926/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/pokemon-is-releasing-some-incredible-merch-for-gold-and-1851700355<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="71d8ee3a9d54719540b9f87f6c659c50" data-recommend-id="image://71d8ee3a9d54719540b9f87f6c659c50" data-format="jpg" data-width="900" data-height="500" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A shot of the full Gold and Silver anniversary colleciton." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A shot of the full Gold and Silver anniversary colleciton." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="71d8ee3a9d54719540b9f87f6c659c50" data-recommend-id="image://71d8ee3a9d54719540b9f87f6c659c50" data-format="jpg" data-width="900" data-height="500" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A shot of the full Gold and Silver anniversary colleciton." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-leak-eevee-flying-evolution-eeveelution-1851685748&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-leak-eevee-flying-evolution-eeveelution-1851685748"><em>Pokémon</em></a></span><em> Gold </em>and <em>Silver</em> turns 25 years old this month. The Game Boy Color RPGs brought fans to the Johto region, introduced 100 new monsters, and are widely considered some of the best games in the franchise’s long history. To commemorate the anniversary, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-center-winter-holiday-merch-christmas-nintendo-1851675507&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-center-winter-holiday-merch-christmas-nintendo-1851675507">The Pokémon Company</a></span> is releasing a new line of merchandise featuring Pokémon and art from the games, and there’s some real tempting stuff in the collection.</p><p>Some of the merch is game-neutral, whereas a few items have been made to spotlight characters and color schemes for either <em>Gold </em>or <em>Silver</em>. The highlights include plushes of game mascots Ho-Oh and Lugia, jackets with a reversible interior design of the Johto region map, and a trash can with the Japanese in-game message you receive when examining trash cans that roughly translates to “Nope, there’s only trash here” printed on it.</p><p>Right now, the line is only going on sale through the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.pokemoncenter-online.com/?srsltid=AfmBOooixSl118ptVAz_Muj67LRmyAGy-hkGhr3M20XUPPFL4uHcvzjX&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.pokemoncenter-online.com/?srsltid=AfmBOooixSl118ptVAz_Muj67LRmyAGy-hkGhr3M20XUPPFL4uHcvzjX" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Japanese Pokémon Center</a></span> website, which always seems to get the best stuff. However, they will no doubt end up on reseller or import sites shortly after the line goes live on November 21. For now, you can click through to see all the merchandise set to go up next week.</p><p>These days, the easiest way to play <em>Gold </em>and <em>Silver </em>is through the 3DS ports released in 2017. I’m still keeping my fingers crossed that Nintendo will one day put the old <em>Pokémon </em>games on Switch and then make a concerted effort to keep these games accessible moving forward, but the company’s lack of care on that front is well-documented.</p><p>Since it’s the 25th anniversary of <em>Gold </em>and <em>Silver</em>, that means it’s also the 15th anniversary of the Nintendo DS remakes <em>Pokémon HeartGold </em>and <em>SoulSilver</em>, which launched during the original games’ 10th anniversary in 2009. Those remakes are still probably the game I’d put at the top of a ranking of the mainline <em>Pokémon </em>games…oh, wait. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/all-the-big-pokemon-games-ranked-from-worst-to-best-1849984595&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/all-the-big-pokemon-games-ranked-from-worst-to-best-1849984595">I did that!</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4a2340dd4c864af38c426ee328d42b7e" data-recommend-id="image://4a2340dd4c864af38c426ee328d42b7e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1500" data-height="1500" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Ho-Oh and Lugia anniversary plushes." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The Ho-Oh and Lugia anniversary plushes." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4a2340dd4c864af38c426ee328d42b7e" data-recommend-id="image://4a2340dd4c864af38c426ee328d42b7e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1500" data-height="1500" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Ho-Oh and Lugia anniversary plushes." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1a2f127bf0c1741df2eed8e05c8aa5be" data-recommend-id="image://1a2f127bf0c1741df2eed8e05c8aa5be" data-format="jpg" data-width="1500" data-height="1500" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Images of the Gold Version anniversary jacket, which has gold sleeves and an image of Ho-Oh on the back, with images of both Lugia and Ho-Oh on the front." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Images of the Gold Version anniversary jacket, which has gold sleeves and an image of Ho-Oh on the back, with i